BEFORE THE RIGHT HON.
BENJAMIN SAMUEL PHILLIPS, LORD MAYOR of the City of London; the Hon. Sir WILLIAM FRY CHANNELL, Knt., one of the Barons of Her Majesty's Court of Exchequer; the Hon. Sir
EDWARD MONTAGUE SMITH , Knt., one of the Justices of Her Majesty's Court of Common Pleas; THOMAS SIDNEY, Esq.; Sir ROBERT WALTER CARDEN, Knt.;
JOHN CARTER , Esq., F.A.S. and F.R.A.S., Aldermen of the said City; RUSSELL GURNEY, Esq., Q.C., M.P., Recorder of the said City; JOHN JOSEPH MECHI, Esq.; JAMES CLARKE LAWRENCE, Esq.; and ROBERT BESLEY, Esq., Aldermen of the said City;
THOMAS CHAMBERS , Esq., Q.C., M.P., Common Serjeant of the said City; and ROBERT MALCOLM KERR, Esq., Judge of the Sheriffs' Court; Her Majesty's Justices of Oyer and Terminer and General Gaol Delivery of Newgate, holden for the said City, and Judges of the Central Criminal Court.
